#!/usr/bin/env bash

lord --verbose << "EOF"
Edit bin/lord so that if AGENTS.md already exists,
it does the commented out behavior of printing and dying out of caution,
but if we pass -f/--force, then it does the current behavior of not
worrying about AGENTS.md already existing, not doing pray > AGENTS.md,
and also not removing AGENTS.md at the end.

EOF
